HEADWORD: Fulgent
<hw>Ful"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fulgens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, <ets>p. pr.</ets> of
<ets>fulgere</ets> to flash, glitter, shine, akin to Gr. <?/ to burn.
See <er>Phlox</er>, <er>Flagrant</er>.]</ety> <def>Exquisitely bright;
shining; dazzling; effulgent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Other Thracians . . . <qex>fulgent</qex> morions wore.</q>
<rj><qau>Glower.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulgently</ent>⟦br⟧
